net.smartcosmos.objects.model.context

Interface IObject

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAccountContext, IAccountDomainResource<IObject>, IDomainResource<IObject>, IMoniker, INamedObject<IObject>, ITypedObject, IUrnNamespace
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ObjectImpl

    public interface IObject
extends IAccountDomainResource<IObject>, INamedObject<IObject>, ITypedObject
    Foundational artifact within the SMART COSMOS Objects platform used to represent nouns, e.g. people, bank accounts, vehicles, parks, buildings, etc.

    All objects are INamedObject instances so that a human-readable INamedObject.getName() can be assigned.

    This is the only class within the SMART COSMOS Objects platform that replaces the system-assigned URN with an arbitrary developer-defined getObjectUrn(). This objectUrn must be unique within the account context. It is up to the developer to devise a URN strategy that meets this requirement.
